<div id="start-div">
    <button type="button" id="start">Click here to get started!</button>
    <div id="welcome-text">
        <h2>Welcome to the world of fishkeeping!</h2>
        <p>When beginner aquarists are planning their first community fish tanks, it can be overwhelming to figure out which fish to choose. There are so many! That's where Aquarium4Noobs can help. You can explore many kinds of fish that will fit in your tank, and see pictures too. Click the button to start planning!</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div id="tank-div" class="hidden">
    <h3>What size is your tank?</h3>
    <button class="gallons" data-gallons="25">25 Gallons</button>
    <button class="gallons" data-gallons="50">50 Gallons</button>
    <button class="gallons" data-gallons="100">100 Gallons</button>
</div>

<div class="hidden" id="main-container">
    <div id="instructions">
        <h3>Now the fun part: Choose your fish!</h3>
        <p>1. Click on a category to see the types of fish that will fit in your tank.</p>
        <p>2. Click on the picture to add it to your tank.</p>
        <p>Repeat until your tank is full!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="column fish-list">
            <div id="fish"></div>
            <div id="subtype"></div>
            {{#each fish}}
            <div class="fish">
                <h4>{{common_name}}</h4>
                <p>Minimum number: {{min_group}}</p>
                <p>Size: {{max_size}} inches</p>
                <img src="{{image}}" width=150 height=150>
            </div>
            {{/each}}
        </div>

        <div id="column tank-container">
            <h3>Your fish tank</h3>
            <div class="main-tank"></div>
            <p id="tankupdate"></p>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>